---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CopyBlock from '../components/CopyBlock.astro';
import Barometer from '../components/Barometer.astro';
import { GITHUB_USER, withBase } from '../lib/site';

// The install script is hosted on this very site (GitHub Pages), so the
// one-liner works without a custom domain. Swap for get.<domain> later.
const installSh = `curl -fsSL https://${GITHUB_USER}.github.io/cardo-app/install.sh | sh`;
---

<Base title="Your pivot point">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Everything in one place.<br />Arranged the way <em>you</em> want it.</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      Cardo is a freely arrangeable dashboard for macOS, Linux and Windows: to-dos, notes,
      calendar, files, timers, a local AI assistant and more than 45 tools – as widgets on your
      personal board. Built for everyone who feels overwhelmed and needs <strong>one</strong> calm
      place where everything comes together. Your pivot point.
    </p>
    <div class="hero__install">
      <CopyBlock command={installSh} label="Install (macOS / Linux)" />
    </div>
    <p>
      <a class="btn" href={withBase('/download#macos')}>macOS (.dmg)</a>
      <a class="btn" href={withBase('/download#windows')}>Windows (.msi)</a>
      <a class="btn" href={withBase('/download#linux')}>Linux (.AppImage)</a>
    </p>
    <p><span class="badge">● 100 % local</span> <span class="muted">Your data never leaves your device. No account, no forced cloud, no tracking.</span></p>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🔒 Local-first, for real</h3>
      <p>Cardo works 100 % offline. Everything lives in an embedded SQLite database on your machine – no server, no account, no telemetry. Zero setup: install, open, done.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🧩 Your dashboard, your rules</h3>
      <p>Start from a blank canvas. Place, move and resize widgets, keep separate pages for work, home and focus. Make it yours with design presets, themes, card styles and fonts. Cardo adapts to how you think – not the other way around.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🧠 A local AI assistant</h3>
      <p>Dump your thoughts, get back proposal cards – appointments, to-dos, notes – applied only when you say yes. It runs 100 % on your device. Prefer cloud power? Bring your own <a href={withBase('/assistant')}>Claude subscription</a> instead. Your choice, every time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>📄 Notes &amp; files that stay yours</h3>
      <p>Write Markdown notes with <code>[[wiki-links]]</code>, backlinks and rendered LaTeX, and browse your notes folder – text, images, PDFs – right inside Cardo. Real files in a folder you own, readable with any editor.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🔑 Sync with your own key</h3>
      <p>Optional, off by default: your to-dos, notes, settings and assistants on every device – end-to-end encrypted with a key only you hold. Carried by your own Google Drive, iCloud/Dropbox folder or WebDAV server. Whoever stores it sees only unreadable blocks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🚦 Transparency traffic light</h3>
      <p>Every tool carries a privacy light: green means it works fully local. Yellow means it contacts the internet – and Cardo tells you in plain language what it sends and where, before anything happens.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>🩺 Checks itself</h3>
      <p>One button in the settings and Cardo runs a full self-test with a readable report. If something is off, you see exactly what – no guessing, no support tickets.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>💙 Free, funded by donations</h3>
      <p>Cardo is free to download and use. If you like it, a voluntary donation helps cover the year's running costs – that's it. No paywalls, no premium tiers.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card honest" style="margin-top:2rem">
    <h3>The honest part</h3>
    <p>
      There is still no Cardo cloud and no account – and that's a feature. Sync is optional and
      works with a key you generate yourself: everything is encrypted on your device before it
      travels through storage <em>you</em> choose (your Drive, your folder, your server).
      Turn it off and Cardo is 100&nbsp;% offline again. Your data is yours, always.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card" style="margin-top:2rem">
    <h3>Support instead of paying</h3>
    <p>
      Cardo is free. If you want to, a donation helps cover the running costs
      (domain, server, certificates) for the current year:
    </p>
    <Barometer />
    <p><a class="btn btn--ghost" href={withBase('/donate')}>Go to the donation page</a></p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .hero em { color: var(--accent); font-style: normal; }
    .hero p { max-width: 640px; margin: 0.75rem auto; }
    .hero .btn { margin: 0.4rem; }
    .hero__install { max-width: 560px; margin: 1.25rem auto 0.5rem; }
    .features { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
